@12935    = ~Black Dragon Scales~
@12936    = ~These heavy scales glisten under the light and are warm to the touch. There are a significant number of them salvaged from the corpse of the Guardian... perhaps they might be useful in the formation of some kind of armor.~
@19912    = ~Can you make anything out of these scales we obtained from the Guardian?~
@19913    = ~The Guardian was a dragon? I remember Iselore talking about the Guardian, but I had no idea what kind of creature he spoke of. Aye, I should be able to make light armor out of these scales. It'll be 5000 gold pieces for the work.~
@19914    = ~Very well, here are the scales and the gold.~
@19915    = ~Maybe another time. Farewell.~
@19916    = ~All done. Here is the armor. Wear it well, friend.~
@1834    = ~Sunscorch
(Evocation)
Level: Drd 1, Rgr 1, Lathander 1, Selune 1
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Reflex half

Upon completion of this spell, a brilliant ray of scorching heat fires down from the sky and burns the target creature for 1d6 + 1 fire damage per level of the caster (to a maximum of 1d6 + 15). Undead, fungi, oozes, and drow and gray dwarves take 1d6 + 2 fire damage per level of the caster (to a maximum of 1d6 + 30). Victims must make a successful Reflex save or be blinded for 3 rounds. Drow and gray dwarves are blinded from the spell for 3 rounds (no save). This spell bypasses the spell resistance of creatures such as drow that are vulnerable to the spell.~
@32204     = ~Charm Person or Animal
(Enchantment) 
Level: Drd 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 4 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 1 Medium-sized or smaller Humanoid or 1 Animal
Saving Throw: Will negates

This spell affects any single person or animal it is cast upon.  The term "person" includes any bipedal human, demihuman, or humanoid of man-size or smaller, such as dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, lizard men, orcs, troglodytes, and others.
Thus, a 10th-level fighter could be charmed, but an ogre could not. If the save is failed, the victim regards the caster as a trusted friend and ally to be heeded and protected.  The caster may give him orders, and the charmed individual will carry them out without question.  Creatures remember everything while charmed and thus will usually be hostile to the caster upon expiration of the spell. The target's Spell Resistance, if any, does not affect this spell.~
@1043    = ~Rainstorm
(Evocation)
Level: Drd 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 2 rounds
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 30-foot radius
Saving Throw: Reflex half

This spell, which may only be cast outdoors, brings forth a magical rain that saturates the area of effect. The rain grants 5/- resistance to fire but a -5 weakness to cold and electricity damage, and deals 8d6 points of cold damage to creatures of Elemental Fire. In addition, all creatures in the area of effect are struck by bolts of lightning that deal 2d6 electricity damage, with a Reflex save for half damage. Flame Blade spells, Shroud of Flame, and salamander auras are also extinguished.~
@1011    = ~Circle of Bones
(Necromancy)
Level: Clr 3
Range: Caster
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 3-foot radius
Saving Throw: None

This spell conjures forth a barrier of floating bones that spin rapidly around the caster. Anyone entering their path takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage and 2d6 slashing damage per round, ignoring spell resistance. This spell does not provoke an attack of opportunity. Circle of Bones cannot be active at the same time as Circle of Blades, as the bones and blades get in each other's way.~
@32405     = ~Mental Domination
(Enchantment) 
Level: Clr 4
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: 1 creature 
Saving Throw: Will negates

This spell enables the caster to invade the mind of the target creature, allowing the caster to will the creature into whatever actions he so desires.  The target creature will resist the effects if a successful Will save with +2 DC is made.  While a creature is dominated in such a manner, its mind is cloudy and thought is hampered - spellcasting is impossible and attack bonuses are made with a -2 penalty. This spell bypasses spell resistance.~
@1021    = ~Smashing Wave
(Evocation)
Level: Drd 5, Rgr 5
Range: 40 feet
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 5-foot wide wave
Saving Throw: Reflex half

This spell summons a wave of water that moves in the direction willed by the caster, striking all in its path with massive force. The wave deals 1d8 crushing damage per caster level (maximum 15d8), and every creature struck by the wave must make a Reflex save or be pushed back and knocked down for 1 round. Creatures of Elemental Fire are extremely vulnerable to this spell, taking double damage. This spell bypasses spell resistance.~
@1023    = ~Circle of Blades
(Evocation)
Level: Clr 6, Pal 5, Helm 6, Tempus 6
Range: Caster
Duration: 2 rounds
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 3-foot radius
Saving Throw: Reflex half

This spell conjures forth a wall of circling, razor-sharp blades that whirl and flash around the caster. Any creature attempting to pass through the blade barrier suffers 10d8 points of damage, bypassing spell resistance, with a successful Reflex save for half damage. This spell does not provoke an attack of opportunity. Circle of Blades cannot be active at the same time as Circle of Bones, as the bones and blades get in each other's way.~
@32608    = ~Sol's Searing Orb
(Evocation)
Level: Clr 6, Drd 5, Rgr 5
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Reflex half

Upon completion of this spell the caster hurls a brilliant, blazing sphere at a target creature. When it hits it explodes in a flash of light, blinding the target creature and dealing 9d12 points of fire damage. A successful Reflex save avoids the blindness and halves the damage. Drow and gray dwarves must make their Reflex save against blindness with +4 DC. Undead creatures are particularly vulnerable to this spell and take double damage. This spell bypasses the spell resistance of creatures such as drow that are vulnerable to it.~
@1592    = ~Sunbeam
(Evocation)
Level: Drd 8, Lathander 7
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 4 rounds
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: Reflex partial

This spell allows the caster to evoke dazzling beams of intensely hot light. Every round, all creatures in the beam are blinded for 3 rounds and take 4d6 points of fire damage, or 16d6 damage over 4 rounds. A successful Reflex save negates the blindness and reduces the damage by half. Drow and gray dwarves take 8d6 damage per round and get no save against the blindness. Undead creatures, fungi, and oozes caught in the ray suffer 1d6 points of damage per caster level (maximum 20d6) per round. This spell bypasses the spell resistance of creatures such as drow that are vulnerable to the spell.~
@34104     = ~Charm Person
(Enchantment)
Level: Brd 1, Sor/Wiz 1
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Will negates 

This spell affects any single person it is cast upon. The term person includes any bipedal human, demihuman, or humanoid of man-size or smaller, such as brownies, dryads, dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, kobolds, lizard men, nixies, orcs, pixies, sprites, troglodytes, and others. Thus, a 10th-level fighter could be charmed, but an ogre could not. The person receives a Will save to avoid the effect.  If the spell recipient fails his saving throw, he regards the caster as a trusted friend and ally to be heeded and protected.  The caster may give him orders, and the charmed individual will carry them out as quickly as possible.
If the caster harms, or attempts to harm, the charmed person by some overt action, or if a dispel magic spell is successfully cast upon the charmed person, the charm spell is broken.  If two or more charm effects simultaneously affect a creature, the most recent charm takes precedence.  Note that the subject has full memory of the events that took place while he was charmed. Also note that you cannot have a charmed creature leave the area where he was charmed. The target's Spell Resistance, if any, does not affect this spell.~
@1681    = ~Color Spray
(Illusion)
Level: Brd 1, Sor/Wiz 1
Range: Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 5' x 20' x 20' wedge 
Saving Throw: Will negates 

This spell creates a vivid, fan-shaped spray of clashing colors to spring forth from the caster's hand. The spell affects each creature caught in the area of effect according to its hit dice:

Up to 2: Unconscious for 5 rounds
3 or 4: Blinded for 3 rounds
5 or more: Stunned for 1 round

A successful Will save will negate the effect. Blind creatures are not affected by color spray. This spell does not provoke an attack of opportunity.~
@34316     = ~Dire Charm
(Enchantment)
Level: Brd 2, Sor/Wiz 3, Bane 3
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 8 rounds
Casting Time: 3 
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Will negates

This spell is similar to the Charm Person spell. However, the affected creature goes into a berserk state, wanting no one to harm his master (the spell caster). Thus, the creature will fight enemies of the caster, even former allies. Dire Charm can affect both humanoids and giants. This spell bypasses spell resistance.~
@1091    = ~Lance of Disruption
(Evocation)
Level: Sor/Wiz 3
Range: 60 feet
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Reflex half

This spell creates a lance of force, extending from the caster to a specified point 60 feet in the distance. Any creatures in the lance's path take 5d4 points of piercing damage, +2 points of damage per level of the caster (maximum of +50). Victims can Reflex save for half damage. This spell bypasses spell resistance.~
@1679    = ~Otiluke's Resilient Sphere
(Evocation)
Level: Sor/Wiz 4
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 4 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Reflex negates

When this spell is cast, the result is a globe of shimmering force that encloses the subject creature. The resilient sphere will contain its subject for the duration of the spell. A non-allied creature can make a Reflex save with +8 DC to dodge the spell. The sphere is completely immune to all damage; the only method of removing the sphere is by the use of a Dispel Magic spell. Hence the creature caught inside the globe is completely safe from all attacks, but at the same time is completely unable to affect the outside world. This spell bypasses spell resistance.~
@1107    = ~Domination
(Enchantment)
Level: Brd 5, Sor/Wiz 6, Bane 5
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 3 rounds / level
Casting Time: 5 
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Will negates 

The domination spell enables the caster to control the actions of any creature while the spell is in effect. This control is maintained through a telepathic link between the caster and the victim. The target gets a Will save with +2 DC in order to avoid the effect. This spell bypasses spell resistance.~
@1814    = ~Mass Dominate
(Enchantment) 
Level: Brd 8, Sor/Wiz 9, Bane 9
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 20-foot radius
Saving Throw: Will negates

This spell forces all creatures not allied with the caster in the area of effect to Will save or be dominated as if affected by the spell Dominate Person. Undead are unaffected by this spell. This spell bypasses spell resistance.~
@36956     = ~Tornado
(Evocation)
Level: Drd 9
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None

A more powerful version of the spell Whirlwind, the spell creates a tornado at the target point that moves randomly. Creatures that come within 15 feet of the tornado get sucked up into it, taking 3d8 slashing damage per second that they stay inside it. Creatures are usually ejected from the tornado after about a round. Huge creatures such as frost giants and dragons aren't sucked up into the tornado but still take damage while in the area of effect. Only one tornado may be active at a time. This spell can only be cast outdoors and bypasses spell resistance.~
@38251     = ~Identify Creature
(Divination)
Level: Brd 2, Drd 2, Rgr 2, Sor/Wiz 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

Identify Creature reveals useful combat information about the target creature. The information includes the creature's level, current and maximum hit points, number of attacks per round, ability scores, resistances, saving throws, and various other traits that depend on the creature. This spell bypasses spell resistance.~
@38653     = ~Boulder Roll
(Conjuration)
Level: Drd 6, Sor/Wiz 6
Range: Special
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: All creatures in path of boulder
Saving Throw: Reflex partial

Boulder Roll creates a large boulder, which rolls forward from the caster, crushing creatures in its path, until it hits a wall. Creatures hit take 12d8 bludgeoning damage and are knocked down for 2 rounds. A successful Reflex save halves the damage and prevents one from being knocked down. The boulder bypasses spell resistance and always travels due south from the caster.~
@38853     = ~Enslave
(Enchantment)
Level: Brd 7, Sor/Wiz 8
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Will negates

This spell allows the caster to permanently gain full control of another creature. The target must make a Will saving throw with +4 DC. If it fails, it is dominated by the caster until it dies or the effect is dispelled. Enslave bypasses spell resistance and can even affect undead and constructs.~
@308    = ~IMPROVED SNEAK ATTACK:

Your sneak attacks are especially deadly.

Prerequisite: 3 levels of rogue per rank in the feat (3, 6, 9, 12, 15)

Benefit: Your sneak attacks deal an additional 1d6 damage. This feat may be taken up to five times.~
@730    = ~DODGE:

You are adept at dodging blows.

Prerequisite: Dex 13+. Taking the feat a second time requires 18 levels of rogue, Dex 25+, Improved Evasion, Defensive Roll.

Benefit: You receive a +1 dodge bonus to armor class against attacks from an opponent.

When taken a second time, the feat also allows you to automatically dodge the first attack that would hit you each round.~
